issue.title: How to compile 2019_R1.1
issue.body:
I want to use openvino as an EP of onnxruntime, and it seems that onnxruntime uses openvino 2019_R1.1(https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/1481). 

I downloaded  source code of 2019_R1.1 from  https://github.com/openvinotoolkit/openvino/releases.
But the file directory seems different from the path which I cloned by git command

I just cd inference-engine; mkdir build; cd build; cmake *****; make -j20" . Compile done 100% But no*.so is generated. it seems someting wrong.

How can I compile the source code of 2019_R1.1 ?
